<SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  CINCINNATI BENGALS VS. BUFFALO BILLS  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  The NFL at a Glance/Week 8  </MEMO>
<TEXT>  TELEVISION/RADIO: ch. 7, 11/KCBS (740).; RECORDS: The Bengals are 0-6 and in
last place in the AFC Central. The Bills are 6-1 and in first place in the AFC
East.; SERIES: Cincinnati leads the series 9-6.; BENGALS UPDATE: Cincinnati QB
Boomer Esiason is 3-1 vs. Buffalo QB Jim Kelly. It's gotten so bad in
Cincinnati that Coach Sam Wyche said he would understand if General Manager
Mike Brown chose to fire him. "Heck, I don't know what the answer is, either,"
Wyche said.; BILLS UPDATE: Rich Stadium has been kind to the Bills, where they
have won 15 straight, including playoffs. This season, Buffalo is averaging 41
points per game at home.; ON MONDAY NIGHT: Both teams are 7-13 on Monday
nights. The Bills' only defeat this season came two weeks ago on Monday night,
33-6 to the Kansas City Chiefs.; KEY INJURIES: Bengals -- RB Eric Ball (ankle)
is questionable. WR Mike Barber (hip) is probable. Bills -- No injuries
reported.  </TEXT>
